    "body": "I think we should actually explain our whole semver syntax in the docs. We do not support all the syntax npm does and we also support some very weird stuff like `X` as a valid version, quoting or `*.*.*`.\r\n\r\nMany examples of valid and invalid pragmas can be found in [`test/libsolidity/SemVerMatcher.cpp`](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/blob/develop/test/libsolidity/SemVerMatcher.cpp) but #11295 shows that we do not have complete coverage of all valid syntax variants.",
